24/08/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- UN Secretary General Kofi Annan is expected to visit Turkey on 6 September as part of a regional trip, the foreign ministry confirmed on Wednesday (23 August). The focus will be on issues related to the Middle East ceasefire resolution and Turkey's potential participation in a UN peacekeeping force in Lebanon, as well as the Cyprus issue. (Ta Nea, Kathimerini - 24/08/06; Zaman, Sabah, NTV, ANA-MPA - 23/08/06)
